I am using Visual Studio Professional 2012, OS Windows 7, 64bit<br />
<br />
When I click on the security tab of the ASP.NET configuration site, I receive the following message:<br />
<br />
Could not load file or assembly 'MySql.Web, Version=6.7.4.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=c5687fc88969c44d' or one of its dependencies. The located assembly's manifest definition does not match the assembly reference. (C:\Windows\Microsoft.NET\Framework\v4.0.30319\Config\machine.config line 258)<br />
<br />
While searching for an answer  I can across the mySql site that said that this was a VS 2012 bug <a href="http://forums.mysql.com/read.php?174,591183,591291#msg-591291" rel="nofollow">http://forums.mysql.com/read.php?174,591183,591291#msg-591291</a> .<br />
<br />
